The HD 83443 Exoplanetary System


Overview

HD 83443 is a star with 0.79 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.94 times its radius. It is located 133.39 light years away from the solar system and is estimated to be 3.2 billion years old, as compared to the Sun which is roughly 4.6 billion years old.

HD 83443 is known to have 1 exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the HD 83443 system


HD 83443 b

HD 83443 b was discovered by the Multiple Observatories observatory, in 2002-10, using the radial velocity method. Its semi-major axis is 0.04 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The mass of HD 83443 b is 108.120 times the mass of Earth. The radius of HD 83443 b is 12.700 that of Earth. At more than 50 Earth masses, HD 83443 b is a gas giant, a planet whose mass is mostly made up of hydrogen and helium, like Jupiter and Saturn in our solar system.
description: 3D visualisation and gravity simulation of the exoplanet system HD 83443, which contains 1 exoplanets and was discovered by the Multiple Observatories.
